                    Alecia A. DeCoudreaux

                    Independent Trustee

                    Alecia A. DeCoudreaux has served as Trustee of the Parnassus Funds since  2013. 
                    She currently serves as a director of CVS Health. Prior to this, Ms. DeCoudreaux 
                    served as the President of Mills College and previously was Vice President and 
                    Deputy General Counsel at Eli Lilly and Company. Ms. DeCoudreaux has served on 
                    many boards, and her experience includes serving as Chair of the Wellesley College 
                    Board of Trustees and service on the Commonwealth Club of California Board of Governors. 
                    Ms. DeCoudreaux is an Honorary Director of the Indiana University Foundation and 
                    Emerita Board Member of the Indiana University School of Law Board of Visitors. 
                    She received her bachelor's degree in English and political science from Wellesley 
                    College and her Juris Doctorate degree from the Indiana University School of Law.
                




                    Donald J. Boteler

                    Independent Trustee

                    Donald J. Boteler serves as Trustee of the Parnassus Funds Trust and the Parnassus
                    Income Funds Trust. He retired in March of 2012 from the Investment Company Institute
                    (ICI), the U.S. mutual fund industry's national trade association in Washington,
                    D.C., where he served as Vice President of Industry Operations from 1993 until his
                    retirement. Mr. Boteler also served as Director of Fund Accounting and Compliance
                    from 1986 to 1993. From 2009 to 2011, he served on the Advisory Council of the International
                    Accounting Standards Board in London. Prior to his ICI career, he served in various
                    roles as a member of the staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and
                    the U.S. Department of Labor. Mr. Boteler received his bachelor's degree in economics
                    and accounting from the University of Maryland and is a member of the American Institute
                    of Certified Public Accountants.
                




                    Jerome L. Dodson

                    Trustee, CEO, Portfolio Manager

                    Jerome L. Dodson founded Parnassus Investments in 1984 and has served as Trustee
                    of the Parnassus Funds Trust and the Parnassus Income Funds Trust since inception.
                    He is the CEO and Chairman of Parnassus Investments and the lead Portfolio Manager of the 
                    Parnassus Fund and the Parnassus Asia Fund. Mr. Dodson is also the sole Portfolio 
                    Manager of the Parnassus Endeavor Fund.  Prior to founding
                    Parnassus Investments in 1984, he served as President and Chief Executive Officer
                    of Continental Savings of America from 1976 to 1982 where he started the "Solar
                    T-Bill" program to finance solar energy installations and also developed innovative
                    programs to finance low and moderate income housing. Mr. Dodson received his bachelor's
                    degree in political science from the University of California, Berkeley and his
                    master's degree in business administration from Harvard Business School.
                






