                        Rachel X. Tan is a Research Analyst. She joined Parnassus Investments in 2012 and
                        was previously a Parnassus research intern. She specializes in integrating environmental,
                        social, and governance research into the firm's investment process. She received
                        her bachelor's degree in economics with a minor in environmental studies from the
                        University of California, Los Angeles where she was a member of the Responsible
                        Investment Action Research Team and BGreen Consulting.
                    







                        Kareem Hammoud

                        Research Analyst

                        Kareem Hammoud is a Research Analyst. He joined Parnassus Investments in 2015 and 
                        was previously a Parnassus research intern. He received his bachelor's degree in 
                        environmental science from the University of California, Berkeley where he was a 
                        member of Berkeley Model United Nations and played intramural soccer. 
                    







                        Robert P. Burmeister

                        Equity Trader

                        Robert P. Burmeister is an Equity Trader. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments
                        in 2009, he was an Analyst at Accenture Consulting where he specialized in risk
                        management for critical assets. Mr. Burmeister received his bachelor's degree in
                        economics from Harvard University and was the co-captain and goalkeeper of the water
                        polo team.
                    









                        Joe Sinha, CIMA®

                        Director of Sales and Marketing

                        Joe Sinha is the Director of Sales and Marketing. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments
                        in 2015, Mr. Sinha served as Senior Vice President and held key leadership roles
                        in sales, marketing strategy, product development, and mergers/acquisitions at Wells
                        Fargo Funds Management, LLC. Prior to Wells Fargo, he held leadership roles in data
                        management and product development at Morningstar, Inc. Mr. Sinha has over 20 years
                        of experience in the mutual fund industry and holds the Series 7, 24, 63, and 66
                        securities licenses. He earned a bachelor's degree in English from the University
                        of Michigan and a master's of business administration from the University of Southern
                        California in product marketing and investment finance.
                    







                        Vidya K. Nathu

                        Manager of Advisor Relations

                        Vidya K. Nathu is the Manager of Advisor Relations. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments
                        in 2008, Ms. Nathu worked for Wells Fargo where she was responsible for creating
                        personalized financial solutions for private clients. She holds the Series 7 and
                        63 securities licenses. Ms. Nathu is an active member of the Financial Women's Association
                        of San Francisco. She received her bachelor's degree in political science from Belmont
                        University and her master's degree in business administration from Lipscomb University.
                    






Scott Liffick
Manager of Institutional Investor Relations

                        Scott Liffick is the Manager of Institutional Investor Relations. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments in 2016, Mr. Liffick served as Vice President and head of west coast index client coverage at MSCI. Prior to this role, he was responsible for MSCI's index relationships with pensions, endowments and foundations, and held various research roles at Gerson Lehrman Group. Mr. Liffick earned a bachelor's degree in Chemical Engineering from Purdue University and a master's of business administration in
                        finance from New York University. He also holds the series 7 and 66 securities licenses and the CAIA designation.
                    







                        Turner Miller, CFA

                        Senior Sales Associate

                        Turner Miller is a Senior Sales Associate. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments in 2015, 
                        Mr. Miller served as Assistant Vice President of Business Management at LPL Financial 
                        where he supported the office of the President. Prior to that, he worked in product 
                        management for LPL. He holds his Series 7 and 66 securities licenses. He holds the 
                        CFA designation and is a member of the CFA Society of San Francisco. He received his 
                        bachelor's degree in business administration from San Diego State University.
                    







                        Constance Scott

                        Senior Marketing Associate / Financial Writer

                        Constance Scott is a Senior Marketing Associate and Financial Writer. Prior to joining 
                        Parnassus Investments in 2015, Ms. Scott was employed as Senior Financial Writer for 
                        AssetMark. She also held progressively responsible positions in marketing at AXA Rosenberg, 
                        including managing editor of the firm's institutional client magazine. Ms. Scott earned a 
                        bachelor's degree in technical and professional writing with a minor in economics at 
                        San Francisco State University, where she graduated summa cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa.
                    







                        Aida Diaz Nunez

                        Marketing Associate

                        Aida Diaz Nunez is a Marketing Associate. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments
                        in 2014, Ms. Diaz worked for Apoyo Financiero as a customer service and loan executive.
                        Previously, she was a Market Research Consultant at Centro Community Partners where
                        she researched the existing barriers to capital within the Latino community in Oakland,
                        California. She holds the Series 7 and 66 securities licenses. Ms. Diaz received her bachelor's degree in business economics with a
                        minor in Spanish and Spanish-American Studies and her master's in business administration
                        from Mills College.
                    






                        Marc C. Mahon

                        Chief Financial Officer

                        Marc C. Mahon is the Chief Financial Officer with responsibility for accounting,
                        finance, and investment operations. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments in 2004,
                        Mr. Mahon worked in senior level investment accounting positions for Paul Capital
                        Partners, Fremont Investment Advisors and Barclays Global Investors. Mr. Mahon is
                        a registered principal and holds the Series 7, 63 and 27 securities licenses. He
                        earned his bachelor's degree in business administration from Arizona State University
                        and his master's in business administration from California State University, Hayward.
                    







                        John V. Skidmore II

                        Chief Compliance Officer, Parnassus Investments
                        Chief Compliance Officer, Parnassus Funds

                        John V. Skidmore is the Chief Compliance Officer of Parnassus Investments and Parnassus Funds. 
                        He joined Parnassus Investments
                        in 2008 and has over 25 years of experience in the investment management industry.
                        He began his mutual fund career with Union Bank of California's HighMark Capital
                        Management subsidiary, where he rose to the position of Vice President and Manager
                        of Mutual Fund Administration. He was also a Vice President with Wells Fargo Funds
                        Management, and prior to joining Parnassus Investments, he was Deputy Chief Compliance
                        Officer at Genworth Financial Wealth Management. Mr. Skidmore is a registered principal
                        and holds the Series 6, 63 and 26 securities licenses, and holds the Investment
                        Adviser Certified Compliance Professional ("IACCP") designation as well as the Certified
                        Securities Compliance Professional ("CSCP") designation. In 2008, Institutional
                        Investor News named him as one of the 20 Rising Stars of Compliance. He received
                        his bachelor's degree in political science and psychology from the University of
                        Kansas. He also has earned a Juris Doctorate degree from Glendale University College
                        of Law, where he was a member of Law Review, and his master's degree in business
                        administration from California State University, Dominguez Hills, where he was a
                        member of the Delta Mu Delta Honor Society.
                    







                        William C. Fraser

                        Director of Shareholder Services

                        William C. Fraser is the Director of Shareholder Services. Prior to joining Parnassus
                        Investments in 1993, Mr. Fraser was a stock broker at Thomas James & Associates.
                        He is responsible for operations and client services. Mr. Fraser is a registered
                        principal and holds the Series 7, 63 and 26 securities licenses. Mr. Fraser received
                        his bachelor's degree in economics from the University of Texas at Austin.
                    







                        Mark Lee

                        Director of Technology

                        Mark Lee is the Director of Technology. He joined Parnassus Investments in 2005.
                        Mr. Lee directs all technology endeavors for the firm and brings expertise in enterprise
                        software, systems integration, web technologies and database applications. His previous
                        experience includes multiple senior consultant and engineering roles in the semiconductor,
                        healthcare and academic industries. He is a proponent for open source projects and
                        a contributor to multiple Java and .NET development groups. Mr. Lee received his
                        bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering and materials science engineering from
                        the University of California, Davis.







                        Stephanie J. Mahon

                        Director of Fund Operations

                        Stephanie J. Mahon is the Director of Fund Operations. Ms. Mahon joined Parnassus
                        Investments in 2005. She has built her career at the firm and manages the accounting
                        and administration of the Parnassus Funds. Ms. Mahon received her bachelor's and
                        master's degrees in business administration from California State University, East
                        Bay.
                    







                        Downey H. Blount

                        Senior Compliance Officer, Parnassus Investments
                        Chief Compliance Officer, Parnassus Funds Distributor

                        Downey Blount is a Senior Compliance Officer of Parnassus Investments and the Chief
                        Compliance Officer of Parnassus Funds Distributor. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments
                        in 2014, Ms. Blount's prior positions included Chief Compliance Officer of Matthews
                        International Capital Management and Mutual Fund Administration Manager at Montgomery
                        Asset Management. Ms. Blount is a registered principal and holds the Series 6, 65
                        and 26 securities licenses. She received a bachelor's degree from U.C. Santa Barbara,
                        and attended law school at the University of San Francisco.
                    







                        Paula M. Benone

                        Manager of Human Resources

                        Paula M. Benone is the Manager of Human Resources. She is responsible for guiding
                        and managing the overall provision of Human Resources services, policies, and programs
                        for the firm. Prior to joining Parnassus Investments in 2015, her 20 years of human
                        resources experience included senior positions within various industries with oversight
                        and accountability for the full employment lifecycle. Ms. Benone is a member of
                        the Society for Human Resource Management and the Northern California Human Resources
                        Association. She received her bachelor's degree in psychology from the University
                        of California, Davis.
                    




                    Alecia A. DeCoudreaux

                    Independent Trustee

                    Alecia A. DeCoudreaux has served as Trustee of the Parnassus Funds since  2013. 
                    She currently serves as a director of CVS Health. Prior to this, Ms. DeCoudreaux 
                    served as the President of Mills College and previously was Vice President and 
                    Deputy General Counsel at Eli Lilly and Company. Ms. DeCoudreaux has served on 
                    many boards, and her experience includes serving as Chair of the Wellesley College 
                    Board of Trustees and service on the Commonwealth Club of California Board of Governors. 
                    Ms. DeCoudreaux is an Honorary Director of the Indiana University Foundation and 
                    Emerita Board Member of the Indiana University School of Law Board of Visitors. 
                    She received her bachelor's degree in English and political science from Wellesley 
                    College and her Juris Doctorate degree from the Indiana University School of Law.
                




                    Donald J. Boteler

                    Independent Trustee

                    Donald J. Boteler serves as Trustee of the Parnassus Funds Trust and the Parnassus
                    Income Funds Trust. He retired in March of 2012 from the Investment Company Institute
                    (ICI), the U.S. mutual fund industry's national trade association in Washington,
                    D.C., where he served as Vice President of Industry Operations from 1993 until his
                    retirement. Mr. Boteler also served as Director of Fund Accounting and Compliance
                    from 1986 to 1993. From 2009 to 2011, he served on the Advisory Council of the International
                    Accounting Standards Board in London. Prior to his ICI career, he served in various
                    roles as a member of the staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and
                    the U.S. Department of Labor. Mr. Boteler received his bachelor's degree in economics
                    and accounting from the University of Maryland and is a member of the American Institute
                    of Certified Public Accountants.
                




                    Jerome L. Dodson

                    Trustee, CEO, Portfolio Manager

                    Jerome L. Dodson founded Parnassus Investments in 1984 and has served as Trustee
                    of the Parnassus Funds Trust and the Parnassus Income Funds Trust since inception.
                    He is the CEO and Chairman of Parnassus Investments and the lead Portfolio Manager of the 
                    Parnassus Fund and the Parnassus Asia Fund. Mr. Dodson is also the sole Portfolio 
                    Manager of the Parnassus Endeavor Fund.  Prior to founding
                    Parnassus Investments in 1984, he served as President and Chief Executive Officer
                    of Continental Savings of America from 1976 to 1982 where he started the "Solar
                    T-Bill" program to finance solar energy installations and also developed innovative
                    programs to finance low and moderate income housing. Mr. Dodson received his bachelor's
                    degree in political science from the University of California, Berkeley and his
                    master's degree in business administration from Harvard Business School.
                






